column4: Animal shelter that provides care for lost or abandoned animals. The organization also offers pet adoptions.
column55: Rabies vaccines are only offered Tuesday-Friday from 2:00 PM - 4:30 PM. Medically necessary euthanasia is offered. However, medical records must be provided. ACAS does not offer boarding or kenneling services to the public.
column66:
Shelter operations that are offered to the public, include medically necessary euthanasia (Must provide medical records), Rabies vaccinations (No other vaccinations are available to the public, and Rabies vaccines are only offered Tuesday-Friday from 2:00 PM - 4:30 PM), county licenses (animal adoption licenses), microchipping, and pet adoptions. A list of adoptable pets is listed on their website.  

Field operations that are offered to the public, include animal cruelty investigations, quarantine of biting animals, nuisance animal complaints, humane education, trapping services for sick, injured or possibly Rabies exposed animals, dangerous dog investigations, sick or injured animals, dog-at-large complaints, Rabies control, complaints for failure to remove animal feces, complaints of failure to confine animals in estrus, animal establishment inspections, and emergency assistance for public safety agencies.  

Services that are offered in-house, include shelter and basic veterinary treatment and vaccinations for sick, injured stray animals waiting for adoption, shelter and care for stray/unwanted animals waiting for adoption, and spay/neuter surgery services for animals that have been adopted by ACAS (Not offered to the public).
column78:
A valid picture ID (driver's license or Florida identification card) is required to complete an application. If the ID does not have the current address, a bill or piece of mail verifying the new physical address must be provided. 

You must verify that your pet has a current Rabies vaccination. All adoptable animals will receive the Rabies vaccination prior to being adopted. If you reside in Alachua County, your dog must have a current license.
column81: Applications are taken on a first-come, first-serve basis. If others have applied prior to your application, they are first in line. Applications must be complete, and approved, prior to adopting any pets.

column4: Community-based organization that is committed to providing a continuum of exemplary services, supports, and advocacy to assure that people with developmental disabilities can enjoy respect and dignity and be full participants within the community.

column66:
Services include, residential settings, transitional living, supported independent living, sheltered employment, mobile work crews, supported employment, community inclusion, and behavioral support. 

Adult Day programs, which offer an opportunity for individuals to acquire and improve skills that will empower them to access activities and relationships of their choice. The Adult Day Training program offers individuals opportunities for work, education, community integration, recreation, and socialization. During these programs, individuals are taught skills needed to work in the community or in the onsite workshop. There are Adult Basic Education classes that are offered through the Alachua County School Board, which are available 4-6 hours per day (During office hours). Individuals may choose the classes that they would like to take based on their interests or needs. Classes that are offered, include cooking, math, reading and writing, personal safety, self-care skills, and arts and crafts. 

There is vocational training offered from a variety of training sites, which include assembly and packaging, general recycling services, secure document destruction, e-waste recycling, and supported employment program. All vocational training inquiries should be directed to Kim Johnson, Arc-2-Work Manager at (352) 334-4060  Ext: 110. 

Local, social gathering events are posted on their website via Arc Calendar. 

LiveScan Fingerprinting, Screening and Photo Capture services are provided. Information is included on their website for scheduling, required documentation, and fees.
